particleLexeme: 1. Used before or after a verb (action) sign to mean the action has happened before the present time, and therefore does not need to happen again, or has happened earlier than you expected. English = already.
verbLexeme: 1. To totally finish doing, making, or producing something. English = complete.
2. To be totally finished with no more work to do or parts to add. English = (be) completed.
